    "ane_backdrop": "The concept of mortals being taken up to heaven without dying has deep ANE roots. In Mesopotamian tradition, Utnapishtim (the flood hero) and his wife are granted immortality and dwell 'at the mouth of the rivers' in a distant paradise. The Sumerian king Enmeduranki, seventh in the antediluvian king list (as Enoch is seventh from Adam), was taken to heaven by the gods Shamash and Adad, where he learned divination and the secrets of heaven and earth. Egyptian pharaohs were understood to ascend to the sky after death to join the circumpolar stars or become one with Ra. The Ugaritic hero Baal ascends to his mountain palace after defeating Mot. What distinguishes the Enochic tradition is its moral dimension: Enoch is translated not because of royal status or divine parentage, but because 'he walked with God' — his translation is the reward of righteousness.",
    
